  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary purpose of this study is to track patient outcomes for bilateral cochlear implant
      recipients in a cohort of 60 children, ages 12 to 36 months at time of surgery, who receive
      two implants in the same operation or in two different surgeries with the initial fitting of
      the devices separated by no more than six months.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
